{
  "name": "Claroty/PANW Alert — Auto Investigation + Verdict-driven Response",
  "description": "Fires automatically on (a) HIGH/CRITICAL Custom STAR alerts whose name contains 'Claroty' (the 5 drift detections — note: STAR alerts do NOT support Purple AI auto-investigation, so for those the workflow only emails + closes/escalates), AND (b) any PANW Firewall Library Detection alert (which DOES support auto-investigation; those events carry claroty_* enrichment so Purple AI correlates PAN behaviour with Claroty asset context before producing a verdict). Steps: (1) capture alert context into local vars; (2) call alertTriggerActions S1/aiInvestigation/run via UAM GraphQL (same as Trigger Purple AI Investigation); (3) email SOC that investigation started; (4) wait 180s; (5) query alert + aiInvestigation back; (6) branch on aiInvestigation.verdict — FALSE_POSITIVE => email + close alert (setAnalystVerdict + setStatus RESOLVED); TRUE_POSITIVE / other => email with verdict, summary, findings and recommendations. PRE-IMPORT: configure the SentinelOne integration connection in Hyperautomation -> Integrations, then re-bind the http_request actions to it (the connection_id below mirrors the one used by the existing Trigger Purple AI Investigation workflow). Replace marc.chisinevski@sentinelone.com with the real distribution list. Verify the aiInvestigation field names in your tenant's GraphQL schema (this workflow assumes 'status', 'verdict', 'summary', 'findings', 'recommendations').",
  "actions": [
    {
